### Chat Feature

#### ChatMessageModel (`lib/features/chat/models/chat_message_model.dart`)
- Properties: id, senderId, receiverId, content, timestamp, isSeen
- Methods: fromJson, copyWith (for updating isSeen), == and hashCode

#### ChatPaginationModel (`lib/features/chat/models/chat_pagination_model.dart`)
- Properties: currentPage, pageSize, hasMore
- Methods: initial constructor, copyWith

#### MessageModel (`lib/features/chat/models/message_model.dart`)
- Simpler model with: id, senderId, senderName, content, timestamp
- Used for generic message display

#### ChatRepository (`lib/features/chat/data/chat_repository.dart`)
- Methods:
  - `getChatHistory(otherUserId, pageNumber, pageSize)`: Fetches paginated messages
    - Handles both raw array and wrapped object responses
    - Reverses messages to oldest-first order
  - `markAsSeen(otherUserId)`: Marks messages from user as read

#### ChatSignalRService (`lib/features/chat/data/chat_signalr_service.dart`)
- Singleton service for real-time chat
- Methods:
  - `connect(token)`: Establishes WebSocket connection with auto-reconnect
  - `disconnect()`: Closes connection and clears callbacks
  - `sendMessage(content, receiverId)`: Sends message via SignalR
  - `sendTypingIndicator(receiverId)`: Sends typing event
- Callbacks: onMessageReceived, onMessageSent, onUserTyping, onConnected, onDisconnected
- Uses FlutterSecureStorage for token retrieval
- Connection options: WebSockets transport, skipNegotiation, auto-reconnect with delays [0, 2000, 5000, 10000, 30000]

#### ChatProvider (`lib/features/chat/providers/chat_provider.dart`)
- `chatProvider`: StateNotifierProvider.family keyed by otherUserId
- `ChatState`: messages, pagination, isLoadingHistory, isLoadingMore, isSending, isConnected, error
- `ChatNotifier` methods:
  - `initialize()`: Connects to SignalR, fetches initial history, marks as seen
  - `loadMoreMessages()`: Loads older messages with pagination
  - `sendMessage(content)`: Sends message with optimistic UI update (temporary message)
  - `sendTypingIndicator()`: Emits typing event
  - `_handleMessageReceived()`: SignalR callback for incoming messages
  - `_handleMessageSent()`: SignalR callback for sent confirmation (replaces temp message)
  - `_handleConnected()`: Updates connection status
  - `_handleDisconnected()`: Handles disconnection
  - `_markMessagesAsSeen()`: Marks unseen messages locally and on server
- Disposal: Clears callbacks but keeps connection (connection closed on logout only)

#### ChatTypingProvider (`lib/features/chat/providers/chat_typing_provider.dart`)
- `chatTypingProvider`: StateNotifierProvider.family keyed by otherUserId
- `TypingState`: isOtherUserTyping, otherUserId
- `ChatTypingNotifier`:
  - Listens to SignalR onUserTyping callback
  - Shows typing indicator only for current conversation partner
  - Auto-hides after 3 seconds of no typing events
  - Uses Timer for auto-hide logic

#### ChatScreen (`lib/features/chat/screens/chat_screen.dart`)
- Features: Real-time chat interface with entrance animations
- Components:
  - `_ChatTopBar`: Shows other user name, connection status (Online/Connecting), back button
  - `ChatListView`: Scrollable message list with infinite scroll, date separators, typing indicator
  - `MessageInput`: Text field with send button, typing indicator with debounce
  - States: Loading, empty, error banner
- Auto-scroll: Scrolls to bottom on new message if near bottom or if user sent message
- Initialization: Calls `chatProvider.notifier.initialize()` in postFrameCallback

#### ChatListView (`lib/features/chat/widgets/chat_list_view.dart`)
- Features:
  - Infinite scroll (triggers load more when 150px from top)
  - Date separators (Today, Yesterday, or formatted date)
  - Typing indicator at bottom
  - Loading more indicator at top
- Uses CustomScrollView with Slivers for performance

#### MessageBubble (`lib/features/chat/widgets/message_bubble.dart`)
- Renders single message bubble
- `isMe = true`: Right-aligned orange gradient bubble with shadow
- `isMe = false`: Left-aligned dark bubble with border
- Shows timestamp and seen status (double tick for seen, single for sent)
- Rounded corners with asymmetric design (message tail)

#### MessageInput (`lib/features/chat/widgets/message_input.dart`)
- Features: Multi-line text field, animated send button, typing indicator with debounce
- Static controller for external access
- Typing debounce: Fires immediately on first keystroke, then throttles to once per 2 seconds
- Send button: Animated scale on press, gradient when enabled, disabled state when empty

#### TypingIndicator (`lib/features/chat/widgets/typing_indicator.dart`)
- Animated "User is typing..." indicator with three bouncing dots
- Staggered dot animation (150ms delay between dots)
- Shows avatar and label above bouncing dots

## UI Design Patterns

### Color Scheme
- Background: `0xFF0A0A0F` (very dark)
- Primary gradient: `0xFFFF6B35` to `0xFFFF3B30` (orange-red)
- Secondary dark: `0xFF111827`, `0xFF1C2333`, `0xFF1F2937`
- Text: White, `0xFFE5E7EB`, `0xFF9CA3AF`, `0xFF6B7280`, `0xFF4B5563`
- Success: `0xFF10B981` (green)
- Error: `0xFFEF4444` (red)

### Common UI Elements
- Background decorations with gradient overlays
- Rounded corners (typically 12-18px)
- Shadows for depth (especially on buttons and cards)
- Entrance animations (FadeTransition, SlideTransition)
- Loading states with gradient containers and spinners
- Error banners with red background
- Empty states with icons and descriptive text

### Animation Patterns
- Fade and slide transitions for screen entrance
- Scale animations on button press
- Animated containers for state changes
- Staggered animations for typing indicator dots
- Smooth scroll to bottom on new messages

## Data Flow

### Authentication Flow
1. User enters credentials on LoginScreen
2. AuthRepository.login() calls API
3. Token stored in FlutterSecureStorage
4. AuthState updated with user info (userId, role, coachId/traineeId)
5. Navigation redirects based on role

### Chat Flow
1. User navigates to ChatScreen with ChatArgs (otherUserId, otherUserName)
2. ChatScreen initializes: connects SignalR, fetches history, marks as seen
3. User types message: MessageInput emits typing indicator (debounced)
4. User sends message: ChatNotifier adds temporary message optimistically, sends via SignalR
5. SignalR confirms: onMessageSent replaces temp message with real message
6. Other user receives: onMessageReceived adds message to their list
7. Messages marked as seen when chat is opened

### Workout Flow (Trainee)
1. TodayWorkoutScreen loads via todayWorkoutProvider
2. If workout exists, shows details and "Log This Workout" button
3. User taps log: navigates to LogWorkoutScreen
4. User enters notes and saves
5. LogWorkoutNotifier calls TraineeRepository.logWorkout()
6. Success: Shows snackbar, navigates back

## API Integration

### REST Endpoints
- All use Dio with authorization header from secure storage
- Handle 204 responses as empty/null
- Support both raw array and wrapped object responses

### SignalR Hub
- WebSocket-based real-time communication
- Methods: SendMessage, SendTypingIndicator
- Events: ReceiveMessage, MessageSent, UserTyping, Connected, Disconnected
- Auto-reconnect with exponential backoff
- Connection shared across chat conversations (singleton)

## State Management Patterns

### Riverpod Providers
- Family providers for per-conversation state (chatProvider, chatTypingProvider)
- FutureProvider for read-only data (todayWorkoutProvider, traineesProvider)
- StateNotifierProvider for mutable state (authStateProvider, logWorkoutProvider, chatProvider)
- Singleton providers for services (authRepositoryProvider, chatSignalRServiceProvider)

### State Updates
- copyWith pattern for immutable state updates
- Clear flags (clearError, clearSuccess) for state transitions
- Optimistic UI updates for instant feedback
- Local state updates before server confirmation

## Navigation Patterns

### GoRouter Usage
- Type-safe navigation with extra parameters
- Route constants in AppRoutes enum
- Context.push() for forward navigation
- Context.pop() for backward navigation
- Post-frame callbacks for initialization after navigation

## Security
- JWT token stored in FlutterSecureStorage
- Token used in Dio authorization header
- Token passed to SignalR via accessTokenFactory
- Token cleared on logout

## Error Handling
- Try-catch blocks in repository methods
- Error state in providers
- Error banners in UI
- Snackbar notifications for user feedback
- Graceful handling of 204/empty responses
